= Internal Factions of the SHP

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The Socialist Left is interested in a pluralist and civil society based democracy, while criticizing the traditional state-centric and elitist structure existing within the party.">Socialist Left</span>!} strength: [+ socialist_left_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ socialist_left_dissent : dissent +]

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The core administrative authority of the party, Social Democrats focus on maintaining stability and the legacy of CHP and the Six Arrows.">Social Democrats</span>!} strength: [+ social_democrats_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ social_democrats_dissent : dissent +]

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The members sympathetic to the People's Labor Party and Kurdish rights, they support the recognition of Kurdish identity, abolition of village rangers and removal of strict state interventions.">Labor Left</span>!} strength: [+ labor_left_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ labor_left_dissent : dissent +]

{!<span class="tooltip-text" title="The New Left aim to reclaim the more traditional Kemalist identity of the old CHP, drawing inspiration from the New Left movement in Europe and Britain, which emphasizes a unitary and growth oriented social democratic framework">New Left</span>!} strength: [+ new_left_strength : strength +], dissent: [+ new_left_dissent : dissent +]

